♪ I'm, I'm doomed

01:35.520 --> 01:40.040
♪ I dunked it, dunked it, in the sauce.
Do you think it's free, I paid for it.

01:40.320 --> 01:42.560
♪ I dunked it, dunked it, in the sauce

01:42.800 --> 01:45.040
♪ I'm doomed, I'm doomed

01:45.120 --> 01:47.280
♪ I dunked, dunked it in the sauce

01:47.520 --> 01:49.760
♪ Do you think it was for free, I paid for it

01:50.000 --> 01:52.680
♪ I dunked, dunked it in the sauce.

01:52.680 --> 01:54.200
(audience applauds)

01:55.760 --> 01:58.680
Now a gorgeous applause to Meli.

01:58.680 --> 01:59.960
(crowd cheering)

02:00.480 --> 02:02.520
Thanks, my principal.

02:03.560 --> 02:07.400
Ladies and gentleman, I am Mademoiselle Coco.

02:07.400 --> 02:09.600
(applause)

02:09.720 --> 02:12.960
I am tonight with you as your M.C.

02:13.040 --> 02:15.480
(applause)

02:15.480 --> 02:19.040
This John invited me and Tunahan to his place.

02:19.240 --> 02:21.000
A small party.

02:21.040 --> 02:22.840
So? Have a good time..

02:23.200 --> 02:25.120
Remzi said you should come with us.

02:26.080 --> 02:27.640
That's funny.

02:27.800 --> 02:29.400
You're hilarious Arzum
(sounds from the stage)

02:29.760 --> 02:32.920
So, you mean while I, wonderful I,

02:33.080 --> 02:35.160
sing like a nightingale on stage

02:35.280 --> 02:39.280
John turns around and invites you
and that Tunahan bitch to a party?
(audience cheering)

02:39.520 --> 02:40.320
Is that it?

02:41.440 --> 02:44.160
Two bitches who flirt around to get a free drink?
(music from stage)

02:44.680 --> 02:45.960
Does that make sense?

02:46.040 --> 02:48.960
Why not? Different tastes, different colors..

02:48.960 --> 02:50.280
Meli: Colors?
Arzum: Besides..

02:50.280 --> 02:52.320
Who are you fucking kidding?

02:52.320 --> 02:55.280
Go tell the John I'm not coming, see what happens.

02:55.560 --> 03:00.480
Don't worry, I'm coming. I'm in the mood for some Champagne.

03:01.120 --> 03:06.120
Please, convey my regrets to Mr. Remzi.
For attaching two ugly bitches to my party

03:06.640 --> 03:10.440
No, no, no.. I think, it's a good idea.

03:11.480 --> 03:15.680
If I'm with two ugly bitches, I will look more attractive.

03:15.800 --> 03:16.800
(Arzum sarcastically discards)

03:20.560 --> 03:21.560
(club music fades out)

03:21.800 --> 03:23.760
(high-heel footsteps)

03:34.240 --> 03:36.040
(urinating)

03:36.400 --> 03:37.400
(baby cries)

03:37.520 --> 03:39.520
(mysterious music)

03:41.240 --> 03:42.640
(baby screams)

03:43.080 --> 03:44.280
(baby crying stops)

03:48.080 --> 03:50.760
(baby coughs)

03:51.760 --> 03:53.240
(baby cries)

04:07.440 --> 04:09.120
(baby crying intensifies)

04:11.040 --> 04:12.960
(footsteps)

04:41.920 --> 04:42.920
(baby stops crying)

04:52.560 --> 04:53.560
(baby gurgles)

04:53.560 --> 04:55.240
Shhhh..

05:05.440 --> 05:06.440
(door closes)

05:12.720 --> 05:13.720
(music fades out)

05:14.360 --> 05:16.920
(door unlocks, baby cries)

05:26.120 --> 05:27.120
(light switch)

05:29.160 --> 05:30.760
(light switch, baby crying)

05:57.800 --> 05:58.800
Please, shhh. Stop it, stop it.

06:00.800 --> 06:02.200
What the hell is going on?

06:02.400 --> 06:03.920
I found it in the trash

06:04.520 --> 06:06.120
What do you mean in the trash?

06:06.280 --> 06:07.960
Some whore threw it in the trash.

06:08.360 --> 06:09.280
What whore?

06:10.160 --> 06:12.600
Its whore of a mother, who else girl?

06:14.320 --> 06:15.720
Unbelievable.

06:16.920 --> 06:19.160
Its little hands are freezing cold.

06:19.160 --> 06:25.160
She could've left it in a park or
something, someone could have found it.

06:25.160 --> 06:29.440
I tried to take off, but then it
was still crying, I couldn't bare it.

06:29.920 --> 06:30.560
Then what?

06:30.760 --> 06:32.080
What do you mean, then what?

06:32.320 --> 06:34.760
I rushed home before it turned into an icicle.

06:34.960 --> 06:37.720
What now? What the hell are we going to do with it?

06:38.400 --> 06:40.680
Play mothers and fathers?

06:40.680 --> 06:41.840
Oh, I don't know.

06:42.240 --> 06:45.480
It can stay for a while, we'll think of something later.

06:45.880 --> 06:47.800
Girlfriend, how do you turn this thing off?
(door creaks)

06:47.800 --> 06:50.880
It will be all quiet, when you wipe its ass and feed it.

06:50.880 --> 06:51.640
Mama

06:51.640 --> 06:53.880
Oh Madame, please shut this thing up.

06:54.360 --> 06:57.760
Aww.. You're upset.

07:01.200 --> 07:03.360
Aww, you have made a stink.

07:03.400 --> 07:04.680
Has it?

07:04.800 --> 07:06.200
Should we look?

07:06.360 --> 07:08.640
Of course you should, you morons.

07:08.920 --> 07:11.640
It won't tell us by itself, will it now?

07:11.960 --> 07:15.000
Ew, that's gross, it shitted itself.

07:15.360 --> 07:17.360
I'm taking you back where I found you.

07:17.360 --> 07:19.560
No, please. Over my dead body

07:20.000 --> 07:22.080
Oh, it's a boy.

07:22.080 --> 07:26.120
Evgenia, go warm up some water.
Let's clean his little bum.

07:27.360 --> 07:28.800
Make sure it's not too hot.

07:30.160 --> 07:31.960
You go warm up some milk.

07:32.320 --> 07:33.600
He must be starving.

07:34.320 --> 07:35.880
And bring my Raki as well.

07:37.520 --> 07:38.760
Poor thing..

07:39.440 --> 07:41.800
So she threw you out on the street, hey?

07:42.240 --> 07:43.840
She must've had a reason.

07:45.000 --> 07:47.920
But she didn't know how sorry she will be.

07:48.440 --> 07:53.120
I didn't know how bad I would feel,
when I gave away my little girl.

07:55.480 --> 07:57.560
I still miss her very much.

07:58.760 --> 08:01.160
Hey Madame, what are you saying to him?

08:01.440 --> 08:04.240
Oh nothing, I was asking about his mother.

08:05.280 --> 08:06.680
Where's the little one?

08:07.920 --> 08:08.680
Gone.

08:10.880 --> 08:12.400
What do you mean, gone?

08:13.320 --> 08:15.400
I left him on the street.

08:17.400 --> 08:18.640
In this cold?

08:19.120 --> 08:20.280
Are you nuts?

08:26.960 --> 08:28.280
You want to kill him.

08:29.240 --> 08:32.760
He's not in the cold anymore, someone took him away.

08:33.520 --> 08:34.440
Who?

08:35.240 --> 08:36.600
Some tranny.

08:36.600 --> 08:40.360
(baby giggles)
Wow that was quick, he was starving.

08:40.680 --> 08:42.480
He's too young to drink milk.

08:42.840 --> 08:45.800
Get some proper baby food and diapers too.

08:47.960 --> 08:50.480
Ok, it's time to burp him now.

08:50.600 --> 08:51.880
What?

08:55.880 --> 08:56.560
(baby farts)

08:56.560 --> 08:57.800
Oh, look at the little man..

08:58.280 --> 09:00.440
Our son is going to be a macho man.

09:00.800 --> 09:04.160
Hey Madame, how does it feel to be a granny?

09:06.680 --> 09:08.000
Cut the crap,

09:08.440 --> 09:09.840
burp your own kid.

09:10.000 --> 09:11.200
My own kid?

09:11.400 --> 09:12.520
It can't be mine,

09:12.720 --> 09:14.520
my hips are too narrow.

09:14.600 --> 09:15.600
(groans)

09:16.160 --> 09:17.880
He's your baby now.

09:17.880 --> 09:19.120
You saved his life.

09:19.280 --> 09:21.800
Sister, you're glowing with motherhood..

09:21.840 --> 09:24.960
It's great, you're a mother now and I'm an aunt.

09:25.160 --> 09:27.360
We have to give him a name.

09:27.920 --> 09:29.320
(nostalgic music)

09:33.960 --> 09:37.520
You are the head of the family, you name him.

09:37.880 --> 09:39.840
You'll be called Deniz

09:40.200 --> 09:42.440
You've had a bad start too.

09:42.640 --> 09:44.880
Your mother regretted she had you.

09:45.040 --> 09:47.400
I pray you'll end up well.

09:47.800 --> 09:49.880
Just like my Deniz.

09:49.920 --> 09:50.920
(seagulls squawking)

09:54.040 --> 09:56.600
(music ends)
Girlfriend, it's too bright out here.

09:56.720 --> 09:58.600
I'm not used to going out this early.

09:59.040 --> 10:01.080
Come on sister, move your ass, he's starving.

10:01.200 --> 10:01.960
Ok, ok.

10:02.560 --> 10:04.000
Make sure you buy the whole list.

10:04.080 --> 10:07.440
Yeah, yeah I will.. Stop nagging. Bye now.

10:07.560 --> 10:08.560
(birds chirping)

10:30.640 --> 10:31.640
(door closes)

10:34.120 --> 10:35.120
(keys rattling)

10:35.400 --> 10:36.400
(keys in lock)

10:48.320 --> 10:49.320
(cello music)

11:23.960 --> 11:26.640
(conversation cannot be heard)

11:43.640 --> 11:44.640
(cello music)

11:58.760 --> 11:59.760
(baby cries)

12:06.520 --> 12:07.520
(baby groaning)

12:13.040 --> 12:14.440
(baby coughs)

12:22.760 --> 12:26.800
"The number you dialled is currently unavailable, please try agai.."

12:27.280 --> 12:29.040
Remzi: You never go home this early.

12:29.080 --> 12:30.680
What's been going on the past few days?

12:31.440 --> 12:32.480
you have a lover?

12:32.520 --> 12:33.680
You are nuts.

12:34.080 --> 12:37.480
I know, I know that you like young pretty boys

12:38.000 --> 12:39.440
Well.. It's up to you..

12:40.240 --> 12:41.640
You'll lose me, okay.

12:42.480 --> 12:44.320
It's that Tunahan bitch, right?

12:44.840 --> 12:46.240
The girl likes me. What can I do?

12:46.560 --> 12:50.360
I don't know what you can do,
but I shall scratch your eyes out.

12:50.520 --> 12:52.040
I will never trade you.

12:52.280 --> 12:53.840
Could I smell another rose?

12:54.240 --> 12:56.920
You'd even smell shit, if there was money in it.

12:57.040 --> 12:59.160
(laughs)
That hurt.

12:59.240 --> 13:00.840
How little you know me.

13:00.840 --> 13:01.960
(laughter)

13:04.560 --> 13:06.520
Meli quick, Deniz is dying.

13:06.600 --> 13:07.720
What's wrong girl?

13:07.800 --> 13:09.800
Deniz has got a very high fever.

13:14.120 --> 13:16.760
(ambulance sirens)
Where's the baby doctor, the baby doctor..

13:16.800 --> 13:18.400
My baby is dying.

13:18.880 --> 13:20.320
"EMERGENCY"

13:20.320 --> 13:25.120
Go to the second floor, turn left, second door on the left.

13:30.680 --> 13:31.680
(door opens)

13:34.600 --> 13:35.720
Lady, wake up.

13:36.040 --> 13:37.360
Where's the doctor?

13:37.560 --> 13:39.160
Where is the doctor?

13:39.240 --> 13:40.240
I'm the doctor.

13:40.240 --> 13:42.560
My baby is dying, he has a fever.

13:42.960 --> 13:43.760
Calm down

13:43.760 --> 13:46.840
While I examine him, you go and register.

13:46.920 --> 13:47.920
(baby groans)

13:49.480 --> 13:51.920
You stay with Deniz, I will do it.

13:54.000 --> 13:55.000
(door closes)

13:55.800 --> 13:59.200
Take his diapers off and lay him on his stomach.

14:04.040 --> 14:06.160
''NAME: M''
(ambulance sirens)

14:06.160 --> 14:07.200
(scribbles)

14:10.760 --> 14:12.160
''NAME: F''

14:15.560 --> 14:17.720
Doctor, what are you doing?

14:17.920 --> 14:19.200
I'm checking his fever.

14:19.280 --> 14:20.600
Have you already checked?

14:21.840 --> 14:22.640
No, but..

14:22.760 --> 14:25.360
Isn't there another way to check?

14:30.440 --> 14:32.360
"NAME: HUMAN"

14:32.360 --> 14:33.720
Doctor: Over 40 degrees..

14:34.320 --> 14:35.840
How long has the child had a fever?

14:36.120 --> 14:37.200
Don't cover him.

14:39.800 --> 14:40.800
I don't know.

14:43.040 --> 14:45.800
Did you notice the child have any convulsions?

14:45.800 --> 14:47.240
Like an epilepsy fit?

14:47.360 --> 14:48.920
I really don't know.

14:48.920 --> 14:52.440
(sighs)
He might have suffered a febrile convulsion.

14:52.440 --> 14:55.000
And if not it may happen in the near future.

14:55.240 --> 14:57.520
What's a febrile convulsion, doctor?

14:57.720 --> 14:58.760
High fever,

14:59.000 --> 15:00.640
can do some damage in the brain.

15:00.880 --> 15:03.640
Which can result in paralysis or another ailement,

15:03.800 --> 15:05.360
in other words, it's very dangerous.

15:05.960 --> 15:07.800
(sobs)
Lord help us.

15:07.880 --> 15:08.880
(sniffles)

15:09.000 --> 15:10.920
What is your relationship to the child?

15:11.000 --> 15:12.360
I'm his aunt.

15:13.120 --> 15:14.120
(door opens)

15:16.960 --> 15:18.800
What's wrong with him doctor?

15:19.120 --> 15:21.000
Whose baby is this?

15:21.400 --> 15:22.240
Ours..

15:22.360 --> 15:23.200
Yours?

15:24.160 --> 15:25.320
Where's his mother?

15:25.760 --> 15:26.400
We don't know.

15:27.200 --> 15:28.560
What do you mean, you don't know?

15:28.600 --> 15:31.480
I found him in the trash can, he was freezing so

15:31.480 --> 15:34.360
I took him home, we're looking after him.

15:34.720 --> 15:36.240
Did you inform the police?

15:37.440 --> 15:38.240
No

15:39.400 --> 15:40.520
You should have.

15:40.680 --> 15:44.400
In this country children without
parents are given to state institutions.

15:45.400 --> 15:47.920
Look doctor, I didn't know this.

15:48.320 --> 15:50.760
If I had known, I wouldn't have taken him.

15:51.320 --> 15:52.920
I swear, I wouldn't have.

15:54.520 --> 15:57.640
If we go to the cops, they'll beat us.

15:57.880 --> 15:59.200
(Evgenia whines and sobs)

15:59.600 --> 16:02.120
If you like, we leave him to you..

16:02.320 --> 16:04.440
You give him to the cops.

16:06.440 --> 16:08.240
Has he had his vaccinations?

16:09.360 --> 16:10.760
We don't know.

16:11.000 --> 16:13.240
Wait a minute, I'll get you the medicine.

16:13.480 --> 16:17.680
If I write you a prescription, you'll just end
up spending money you probably don't have.

16:18.160 --> 16:20.200
We're always given free samples.

16:20.200 --> 16:21.200
Wait for me.
(Evgenia crying)

16:26.040 --> 16:27.200
Stop crying, girl.

16:27.400 --> 16:29.000
Take this and hide Deniz in it.

16:29.520 --> 16:32.480
Get the hell out of here before the bitch comes with the cops.

16:33.840 --> 16:36.600
Don't use the main door, use one of the back doors.

16:37.520 --> 16:39.800
Get in a taxi and go straight home.

16:40.840 --> 16:42.200
(suspense music)

16:49.760 --> 16:51.720
Come on, go.

17:06.880 --> 17:07.880
(sirens)

17:18.920 --> 17:20.360
(heavy breathing)

17:41.800 --> 17:43.360
Taxi.

17:45.320 --> 17:46.920
(taxi breaks)

17:55.240 --> 17:56.720
(exhales a deep breath)

17:57.800 --> 18:02.080
Take me to Galata baby.
Step on it, I've got a patient waiting.

18:10.680 --> 18:11.720
There, you are.

18:12.120 --> 18:13.480
Here..
(plastic bag ruffling)

18:14.640 --> 18:18.360
Look, I thought it will be
best that you keep the baby for now.

18:18.800 --> 18:21.320
But you have to keep him under constant observation.

18:21.600 --> 18:22.880
Thank you, doctor.

18:23.160 --> 18:25.000
I wrote the instructions on the medicine.

18:25.440 --> 18:26.840
You have to get the fever down.

18:27.080 --> 18:29.960
Soak a towel in vinegar and put it on his forehead

18:30.160 --> 18:32.320
and keep an eye on him at all times.

18:32.760 --> 18:34.760
It's possible he'll have convulsions.

18:35.280 --> 18:38.280
If this happens, bring him to the hospital at once.

18:38.760 --> 18:41.200
I won't report you to the police on one condition,

18:41.680 --> 18:44.120
you will be in contact with me at all times.

18:45.120 --> 18:48.400
And bring the baby to my
private office on Friday at 10 A.M.

18:50.600 --> 18:52.320
You'll come on Friday, right?

18:53.200 --> 18:53.800
Promise?

18:54.080 --> 18:54.800
Promise.

18:55.320 --> 18:58.720
Look, if you do not come, this child may be harmed,

18:58.960 --> 19:01.800
and you will be legally responsible.

19:02.280 --> 19:03.280
(sniffles)

19:13.200 --> 19:14.200
(door unlocks)

19:17.320 --> 19:18.320
(lets out a deep breath)

19:25.720 --> 19:28.600
(sighs)
Oh god, I'm dead..

19:30.440 --> 19:31.920
(exhales)

19:36.240 --> 19:37.240
What?

19:37.320 --> 19:39.520
Have you been playing doctor with the clients?

19:39.640 --> 19:42.440
Johns have sure changed over the years.

19:42.520 --> 19:46.360
In my time, they used to
drink Champagne from our shoes.

19:46.360 --> 19:50.160
At the most, they'd ask you to keep
your garters and stockings on.

19:50.200 --> 19:52.400
What the hell are you talking about, Madame?

19:52.400 --> 19:54.400
I've just escaped hell..
(door opens)

19:57.160 --> 19:58.560
Meli: Where have you been?

19:59.200 --> 19:59.680
Mama

19:59.880 --> 20:02.160
You will never believe what we've just been through.

20:02.240 --> 20:04.320
They almost took Deniz away from us.

20:04.720 --> 20:06.480
What happened? Spit it out.

20:09.000 --> 20:11.840
Early in the morning, Deniz had a fever.

20:11.920 --> 20:14.600
Of course, he was out on the street, freezing.

20:14.640 --> 20:16.800
Meli and I brought him to the hospital.

20:17.000 --> 20:19.000
Oh , I was wondering where you came from.

20:19.120 --> 20:23.200
They told us, you have to go to the
cops when you find a baby in the street.

20:23.320 --> 20:26.520
Obviously, it's not a stray kitten, is it?

20:27.320 --> 20:30.120
If you knew, why didn't you tell me in the first place?

20:32.160 --> 20:33.600
(baby moaning)

20:35.040 --> 20:38.440
Evgenia, put the kid to bed.
If he's sick, he should be in bed.

20:38.440 --> 20:41.080
I'll do it. He's my son.

20:43.080 --> 20:46.600
The doctor said, he may have febrile convulsion.

20:46.640 --> 20:48.000
Febrile convulsion?

20:48.400 --> 20:50.480
Aylin: I wish I'd never done it.

20:53.160 --> 20:54.680
(sounds from the city)

20:58.640 --> 21:00.360
No use now.

21:01.560 --> 21:03.560
I'll get him back.

21:11.600 --> 21:13.200
It's been three days.

21:14.560 --> 21:16.160
How can you find him?

21:16.480 --> 21:18.880
I will find him, I know that.

21:20.240 --> 21:23.840
(sighs)
But I don't know what the
fuck I'm gonna do after I find him.

21:24.520 --> 21:26.000
I don't have a penny.

21:26.200 --> 21:28.840
I haven't worked for months now.

21:34.720 --> 21:35.960
You find the kid.

21:36.000 --> 21:37.400
Don't worry about the money.

21:38.000 --> 21:39.480
How?

21:39.680 --> 21:44.200
I still haven't recovered from the birth, I can't work.

21:45.320 --> 21:48.840
(Evgenia sniggers)

21:51.200 --> 21:53.520
Hey sister, what's with this?

21:53.840 --> 21:56.960
What's with this? What do you think?

21:57.120 --> 22:00.240
Do you think it was easy to get out
of that fucking hospital?

22:01.680 --> 22:04.720
We must bring this kid back
where I found him, right now.

22:05.080 --> 22:08.960
No, no, that doctor, she's
good. She didn't go to the cops.

