the incident every time he saw me.

40:28.760 --> 40:31.360
Then he would get angry and take it out on her.

40:31.800 --> 40:33.560
Mothers don't love their children.

40:33.920 --> 40:37.720
They just bear them to satisfy their own selfish insticts.

40:38.640 --> 40:40.320
Put the kid in his bed.

40:41.320 --> 40:42.520
It's late.

40:51.280 --> 40:52.480
Madame is upset.

40:52.760 --> 40:55.960
She's realised how selfish she
was to raise you like a girl.

40:55.960 --> 40:58.720
Come on sister, I told you, she's not my real Mama.

40:58.920 --> 41:01.320
Like shit you did, you told me nothing.

41:01.760 --> 41:03.920
You just keep saying she's not your mother.

41:04.680 --> 41:09.360
I can't ask the details not to
upset you, but I am dying of curiosity.

41:09.760 --> 41:11.960
Will you just fucking tell me and get it over with?

41:14.440 --> 41:15.440
(sighs)

41:15.760 --> 41:18.240
But, you will never tell Mama.

41:18.720 --> 41:20.440
I won't, go on.

41:22.600 --> 41:25.760
My Mama and Madame Despina were really close friends.

41:25.840 --> 41:28.760
She used to always come over and comfort Mom.

41:28.960 --> 41:30.560
Why would she comfort her?

41:31.040 --> 41:35.280
After my Dad took off, Mama was in mourning.

41:36.000 --> 41:37.560
She used to cry every day.

41:37.560 --> 41:40.480
Poor thing, that's the dark side of love.

41:40.920 --> 41:43.320
That's what Mama Despina used to say.

41:43.400 --> 41:47.120
She would say: good for
nothing bum, took all your money

41:47.120 --> 41:51.680
and now with this hopeless love,
he's taking all your beauty away.

41:52.160 --> 41:53.880
Was your Mom a whore, too?

41:53.880 --> 41:57.680
I don't know, no man ever entered the apartment

41:58.160 --> 42:01.160
but, I don't think she was an angel.

42:01.440 --> 42:06.240
Otherwise, where could she get money to buy this apartment?

42:07.120 --> 42:09.840
How could Dad take her money?

42:10.440 --> 42:11.320
True.

42:11.440 --> 42:15.440
She didn't have any relatives
that I knew, only Mama Despina.

42:15.760 --> 42:19.080
I think she was providing for us at the time.

42:19.400 --> 42:23.920
Sometimes, she used to come with this little girl,

42:24.040 --> 42:28.080
she had green eyes, fair hair, she was nice.

42:28.120 --> 42:29.440
We used to play.

42:29.600 --> 42:32.160
Then, she disappeared one day.

42:32.200 --> 42:33.960
What happened to your real Mom?

42:33.960 --> 42:36.240
One day, there was a lot of joy.

42:36.240 --> 42:38.560
Mom found out where Dad was.

42:39.280 --> 42:41.840
He had opened a bar in Beirut.

42:42.280 --> 42:44.240
She said: we are going.

42:44.840 --> 42:47.280
She put the house up for sale.

42:47.400 --> 42:51.440
Mama Despina said: don't be
crazy, you will ruin the childs life.

42:51.840 --> 42:53.720
She's right. Then?

42:54.040 --> 42:57.360
Then, Mama Despina bought the house from my Mom

42:57.760 --> 43:03.240
and she wouldn't let me go,
she took care of me and looked after me,

43:04.040 --> 43:04.120
but she never told me she bought the house.

43:04.120 --> 43:08.000
but she never told me she bought the house.

43:08.400 --> 43:11.440
She always says: this is your house.

43:11.560 --> 43:12.560
And your Mom?

43:12.680 --> 43:13.880
She went to Beirut.

43:14.760 --> 43:17.480
That's why I think Mama Despina bought the house.

43:17.640 --> 43:21.800
Otherwise, where would mum have
found the money to pick up and go?

43:22.040 --> 43:23.520
Haven't you heard from her?

43:23.520 --> 43:25.400
Yes, she sent a letter.

43:26.160 --> 43:27.760
She had found my Dad.

43:27.880 --> 43:29.880
She said they were happy.

43:30.040 --> 43:33.360
She said they would come and get me soon.

43:33.920 --> 43:37.720
Then, no more letters, no more news

43:38.160 --> 43:41.080
and a war started in Beirut.

43:41.800 --> 43:43.600
Maybe she died.

43:46.520 --> 43:49.720
See? Another example of selfishness.

43:50.040 --> 43:52.120
Mothers don't have the right to die.

43:52.120 --> 43:55.160
If your'e going to die, why have children?

43:56.320 --> 43:57.800
(sighs)

43:58.160 --> 44:01.480
Where did this tranny disappear to?

44:03.800 --> 44:06.200
You can't find those people during the day.

44:06.680 --> 44:09.720
They work at night, and sleep all day.

44:10.160 --> 44:16.000
We have to look for him at night or very early in the morning.

44:16.800 --> 44:17.600
Of course.

44:17.600 --> 44:18.600
Yeah.

44:19.480 --> 44:21.480
Stupid me.

44:21.960 --> 44:24.360
How couldn't I think of this?

44:25.080 --> 44:28.320
It was 4 in the morning, when she found my baby.

44:28.320 --> 44:31.920
Aylin: She was going back home from work.
(dance music playing from club)

44:40.120 --> 44:41.320
You're leaving early again.

44:41.320 --> 44:42.280
(cries out)

44:42.320 --> 44:44.880
It's you Remzi. You scared the hell out of me.

44:45.040 --> 44:45.920
What's up?

44:45.920 --> 44:47.040
Where are you going?

44:47.120 --> 44:49.440
I feel a little sick, I told the boss I..

44:49.440 --> 44:50.440
You are sick, hey?

44:50.880 --> 44:52.240
Who are you kidding?

44:52.240 --> 44:54.360
You have found someone new, haven't you?

44:54.360 --> 44:56.800
Don't start with this bullshit again, Remzi.

44:58.760 --> 44:59.800
Look, Remzi,

45:00.120 --> 45:01.360
I'll be frank.

45:01.480 --> 45:03.440
I have to change my life.

45:03.440 --> 45:04.680
Now..
Remzi: Now what?

45:04.680 --> 45:05.400
Look..

45:06.560 --> 45:10.560
The last few months, I have a completely
different kind of love in my life.

45:10.760 --> 45:12.440
What do you think I am? A schmuck?

45:13.200 --> 45:14.600
Please don't get nasty.

45:14.720 --> 45:15.280
You've got me wrong.

45:15.280 --> 45:16.920
You get me wrong, baby.

45:17.160 --> 45:19.440
I won't let someone else take your money, okay?

45:19.440 --> 45:20.080
Damn you.

45:20.160 --> 45:21.520
It's just the money hey?

45:21.720 --> 45:24.440
At least don't say it to my face, you bastard.

45:24.440 --> 45:26.400
(Screams)

45:26.400 --> 45:27.760
Don't hit me.

45:27.800 --> 45:28.800
(Screams and Slapping)

45:29.840 --> 45:31.680
(running foot steps)

45:31.800 --> 45:33.240
(crying)

45:51.840 --> 45:52.840
(key in door)

45:55.640 --> 45:57.160
I found the tranny.

45:57.440 --> 45:58.160
Great.

45:58.160 --> 45:59.880
Does he still have the baby?

46:05.680 --> 46:07.040
(hard slap on the back)

46:07.960 --> 46:08.520
Come here.

46:08.520 --> 46:09.760
Sit down.

46:15.600 --> 46:16.840
Listen loser.

46:17.520 --> 46:20.840
I told you I'm in a hurry to finish with this joint,

46:21.040 --> 46:24.440
so I won't waste time with you as well, you hear?

46:25.400 --> 46:27.640
How will she go on stage like this?

46:27.760 --> 46:29.000
I'm sorry, boss.

46:29.200 --> 46:32.080
She hit me you see, I lost control.

46:34.960 --> 46:36.480
Hear me out, faggot.

46:36.840 --> 46:42.120
I don't go around hitting people,
like you do. If you catch my drift?

46:42.600 --> 46:46.280
Believe me, boss, I'm really sorry, I really regret it.

46:47.720 --> 46:49.520
Please forgive me darling.

46:49.720 --> 46:52.000
(sobbing)
Believe me, I really regret it so much.

46:53.480 --> 46:55.240
I couldn't sleep at all last night.

47:12.720 --> 47:15.440
Perverts, the bunch of them.

47:27.960 --> 47:31.240
Mama, are you taking another trip through nostalgia?

47:31.680 --> 47:34.720
The sun of reminiscence never sets, Evgenia,

47:35.840 --> 47:43.000
I can now see that I have lived such
a mad,sad, but just as happy life.

47:46.680 --> 47:50.560
Don't upset yourself, you don't want another heart attack.

47:50.840 --> 47:56.920
Life has no meaning without the sorrow
of the past that will never return.

48:00.920 --> 48:03.360
You're also drinking too much mama.

48:03.360 --> 48:06.360
Well, the doctor says it's good for me.

48:06.640 --> 48:08.600
It opens the veins.

48:08.920 --> 48:11.200
I will go and wake Meli up.

48:11.400 --> 48:13.720
We'll take Deniz to the park.

48:20.480 --> 48:23.360
Pick me up a bottle of Raki on your way back.

48:25.520 --> 48:26.520
(door opens)

48:28.480 --> 48:32.480
Sister, I forgot my sunglasses, go get them.

48:34.960 --> 48:36.320
(door opens)

48:37.200 --> 48:39.880
The bitch has really settled in now.

48:40.880 --> 48:41.880
(door opens)

48:46.440 --> 48:48.600
(birds singing)

49:15.600 --> 49:16.640
Don't look, girl.

49:17.080 --> 49:19.360
What do you see in that fiddler? I never know.

49:19.560 --> 49:23.160
It's not a fiddle sister, it's a cello or something.

49:23.320 --> 49:24.640
Cello, schmello

49:25.000 --> 49:26.760
They're all fiddles anyways.

49:27.400 --> 49:29.240
Oh come on, sister. Give me a break.

49:29.240 --> 49:31.760
(children laughing)

50:02.480 --> 50:05.040
Look at that woman sitting alone over there.

50:05.400 --> 50:07.080
I think she is watching us.

50:07.960 --> 50:09.960
So what? everybody stares at us.

50:09.960 --> 50:14.160
No, this one's watching us differently. Look carefully.

50:23.400 --> 50:27.000
No, look, she's going anyway.

50:33.800 --> 50:35.680
She kept looking at Deniz.

50:35.880 --> 50:38.160
She will give him the evil eye.

50:39.080 --> 50:40.880
(knocks on wooden bench)

50:43.760 --> 50:46.160
(children playing)

50:52.440 --> 50:54.440
Oh shit, Mama's Raki

50:54.520 --> 50:57.120
Girl, that's the woman in the park,

50:57.120 --> 50:58.600
she's following us.

50:58.720 --> 51:00.440
Come on sister, what the hell?
(suspense music)

51:00.440 --> 51:02.080
Come on, girl.

51:26.200 --> 51:28.320
(suspense music ends)

51:31.000 --> 51:34.760
(mischievous music)
Fuck the stupid woman, let's go get Madame's Raki

51:35.400 --> 51:38.440
We could get it from Husam's store.

51:38.440 --> 51:42.840
No, no, we will get it from
Mahmud, his Raki is very good.

51:44.480 --> 51:47.640
And fuck the fiddler of yours, too. Come on.

51:48.520 --> 51:49.440
(baby laughs)

51:52.960 --> 51:54.240
(music ends)

51:55.600 --> 51:57.040
I found my son.

51:57.400 --> 51:59.000
He's still with the tranny.

52:00.200 --> 52:01.760
I have great news, too.

52:01.760 --> 52:03.320
I'm going to have an exhibition.

52:03.320 --> 52:04.440
A gallery called.

52:04.480 --> 52:06.480
He has grown up so much.

52:06.480 --> 52:07.200
Great.

52:07.200 --> 52:09.040
You see, everything is looking up.

52:09.520 --> 52:10.840
He looks happy

52:10.840 --> 52:12.760
and his health seems to be okay.

52:13.200 --> 52:15.040
God bless that tranny.

52:16.600 --> 52:17.600
Oh..Ah

52:17.920 --> 52:18.920
(laughs nervously)

52:18.960 --> 52:20.920
It's so lovely.

52:21.720 --> 52:22.880
Does it suit me?

52:23.000 --> 52:27.960
Of course, you are really
beautiful. Anything will suit you.

52:30.320 --> 52:32.240
Thank you very much.
(baby giggles)

52:32.240 --> 52:33.920
Thank Evgenia for me.

52:33.920 --> 52:36.240
Thank you, little boy with my name.

52:40.520 --> 52:42.600
See you next week doctor.

52:44.160 --> 52:45.360
Meli..

52:45.400 --> 52:47.400
You love him now, don't you?

52:48.800 --> 52:53.400
Yes doctor. Very much. More than anything.

52:53.960 --> 52:56.840
Listen, I live directly above the clinic.

52:57.200 --> 53:02.080
Let me give you my number, if anything
comes up you can call me anytime.

53:05.640 --> 53:06.400
There you go.

53:06.400 --> 53:08.000
Thank you.

53:08.000 --> 53:09.480
(Suzan laughing)

53:09.840 --> 53:11.600
Disgusting.

53:13.520 --> 53:14.680
Maybe,

53:14.920 --> 53:17.520
but it's not the blouse that counts, it's the thought.

53:18.160 --> 53:20.200
That's why I still see him.

53:21.040 --> 53:24.680
Just the love he gives to a baby who was
thrown on the street by his own mother,

53:24.680 --> 53:27.920
shows that he's more human than many people I love.

53:28.680 --> 53:30.040
What are you trying to say?

53:30.600 --> 53:32.640
Are you insinuating that I'm less?

53:32.760 --> 53:34.840
No Suzan, of course not.

53:34.960 --> 53:37.480
I'm sorry, I'm a bit distracted.

53:37.640 --> 53:40.320
I can see that, that's why I asked.

53:40.880 --> 53:42.840
Why don't you talk to me?

53:43.360 --> 53:46.000
Has it got anything to do with Uncle's visit?

53:46.240 --> 53:48.200
No.. I told you.

53:48.200 --> 53:52.040
Dad was here for business, our
meeting was a coincidence.

53:52.240 --> 53:53.240
Infact,

53:53.760 --> 53:56.640
there's no reason why I should be distracted.

53:59.760 --> 54:01.920
Maybe, there is.

54:02.120 --> 54:04.480
I think I know why I'm all nerves.

54:06.280 --> 54:07.320
There's this man.

54:08.200 --> 54:09.200
A surgeon.

54:09.240 --> 54:10.120
And?

54:11.200 --> 54:13.120
And, I like him.

54:13.280 --> 54:14.720
What's his name?

54:15.160 --> 54:15.760
Jan.

54:16.400 --> 54:18.920
I have two tickets for a concert on Saturday night.

54:19.080 --> 54:20.160
Classical music.

54:20.320 --> 54:22.440
If you don't like it, we can go somewhere else.

54:22.520 --> 54:23.960
I like classical music.

54:32.520 --> 54:33.880
What are you doing, girl?

54:33.880 --> 54:35.400
I'm hanging the curtains.

54:35.440 --> 54:39.400
I open the window a bit and they dry in no time.

54:40.000 --> 54:40.880
Let me help you.

54:40.880 --> 54:43.240
No, no, you'll be late for work.

54:43.280 --> 54:44.080
I have time,

54:44.080 --> 54:45.880
I don't want to go to work, anyway.

54:46.440 --> 54:47.120
Why?

54:47.800 --> 54:50.200
It's Saturday, the club will be packed.

54:50.200 --> 54:52.920
Have to entertain the crowd till morning.

54:53.880 --> 54:57.400
It's weird with Remzi, after that fight..

54:57.400 --> 55:03.080
(screams and crash)

55:03.080 --> 55:05.480
(groaning)

55:06.000 --> 55:08.840
What are you trying to do girls? Wreck the house?

55:08.920 --> 55:11.400
Don't shout, Mama, you'll wake Deniz.

55:11.400 --> 55:12.720
Are you joking?

55:12.720 --> 55:17.720
My shout is nothing compared to the noise you've made.

55:17.760 --> 55:21.600
Oh my god, it took me ages to put him to sleep.

55:21.640 --> 55:24.880
(heavy breathing)

55:28.200 --> 55:29.360
Ah..

55:33.240 --> 55:36.320
Thank God, he's still asleep.

55:39.240 --> 55:41.360
What's the matter?

55:41.800 --> 55:42.840
(Whispering)
He is deaf.

55:42.840 --> 55:44.440
Who's deaf?

55:44.600 --> 55:46.840
Who else girl? Deniz.

55:47.200 --> 55:49.520
The expected disaster has struck.

55:49.520 --> 55:52.160
(loud crying and wailing)

56:02.120 --> 56:03.600
We are doomed Madame.

56:03.600 --> 56:05.200
What's wrong?

56:05.200 --> 56:05.800
(crying)

56:05.800 --> 56:07.120
Deniz, Mama.

56:07.240 --> 56:10.000
Don't drive me mad, girls.
What's wrong with the kid?

56:10.080 --> 56:12.800
He's maimed, Madame, he's gone deaf.

56:13.480 --> 56:16.160
He won't be able to speak all his life

56:16.360 --> 56:19.720
My poor baby will live in a silent world

56:20.000 --> 56:23.760
not hearing a sound, not speaking a word.

56:23.760 --> 56:24.880
(wailing)

56:25.120 --> 56:26.920
You said he's gone deaf.

56:27.400 --> 56:28.960
Why can't he speak?

56:28.960 --> 56:34.080
Idiot. How will he be able to
learn how to speak, if he can't hear?

56:34.120 --> 56:36.680
(wailing)

56:39.800 --> 56:41.320
For shit sake.

56:41.520 --> 56:42.840
Will you tell me what's going on?

56:42.960 --> 56:45.600
Madame, Deniz didn't wake up with all that noise,

56:45.800 --> 56:46.680
he's gone deaf.

56:46.680 --> 56:48.120
Oh come on.

56:48.200 --> 56:50.120
How did you come to that conclusion?

56:50.400 --> 56:53.680
We didn't, Madame, the doctor already told us that

56:53.680 --> 56:56.520
high fever could have done some damage to the brain.

56:57.160 --> 57:00.000
She was expecting some disorder anytime.

57:00.000 --> 57:05.160
Bullshit. Then you can take him
to her, she can examine the child,

57:05.440 --> 57:07.120
see if he's deaf.

57:08.120 --> 57:10.480
What, are you doctors now?

57:11.120 --> 57:12.200
Thank you, Madame.

57:12.440 --> 57:13.720
You are so clever.

57:15.200 --> 57:17.480
Where the hell did I put her number?

57:18.640 --> 57:24.360
Meli, please. Stay calm. What's the
point of bringing the child here?

57:24.360 --> 57:26.280
There's nothing I can do now.

57:29.560 --> 57:32.440
Meli. You're being ridiculous.

57:33.080 --> 57:35.880
I said, bring him to the hospital on Monday.

57:36.280 --> 57:37.040
Calm down.

57:37.040 --> 57:38.320
Good night

57:40.520 --> 57:42.000
Damn woman.

57:42.200 --> 57:43.920
She's playing dirty on me now.

57:45.960 --> 57:47.360
Would you believe that?

57:47.760 --> 57:51.200
Fuck my brains, I will never learn.

57:52.000 --> 57:54.240
I trust everybody.

57:56.160 --> 58:01.200
You remember you said to me she was good
woman? And I said like shit she is, remember?

58:02.000 --> 58:04.240
I told you, then I went and believed her.

58:04.760 --> 58:06.200
Could you imagine that?

58:06.400 --> 58:07.720
Fuck my brains.

58:08.880 --> 58:10.040
What shall we do now?

58:10.320 --> 58:12.440
Meli, Pediamu (my child)

58:12.720 --> 58:17.040
Calm down, be rational.

58:18.760 --> 58:20.840
Tell us, what did she say?

58:21.080 --> 58:23.080
There's nothing to be done now, she said.

58:23.080 --> 58:26.000
She said, we should take
Deniz to the hospital on Monday.

58:26.000 --> 58:28.520
Well, she is a doctor, isn't she?

58:28.640 --> 58:30.200
She might be right.

58:30.200 --> 58:31.560
Think calmly.

58:32.200 --> 58:34.200
How can I think calmly, Madame?

58:34.720 --> 58:36.680
How will I go through this night?

58:37.800 --> 58:39.800
How can I wait for Monday?

58:40.160 --> 58:44.040
Of course, she is fine. That's not her child,

58:44.200 --> 58:47.720
the child is not with her.

58:49.120 --> 58:50.760
(quiet crying)

58:51.920 --> 58:53.120
Come on girl, let's go.

58:53.400 --> 58:58.240
Meli, where are you going? Don't
do anything rash. Endaksi (Alright)?

58:58.240 --> 59:01.440
Don't worry Madame, I'm doing what's best for Deniz.

59:01.800 --> 59:03.640
(doorbell rings)

59:03.640 --> 59:05.840
Here he is, I'm dying to see this man.

59:05.880 --> 59:07.560
Go and open the door.

59:20.120 --> 59:21.280
(door slams)

59:33.520 --> 59:34.320
Damn him.

59:34.320 --> 59:35.400
Who, Jan?

59:35.600 --> 59:36.000
No.

59:36.240 --> 59:36.680
Who then?

59:37.200 --> 59:38.120
What the hell is going on?

59:38.120 --> 59:39.680
Go and see for yourself.

59:39.880 --> 59:41.680
God, how will I find him?

1:00:01.360 --> 1:00:05.080
Deniz, won't you tell me what's going on? Who is this baby?

1:00:05.320 --> 1:00:06.920
Meli's baby, who else?

1:00:06.960 --> 1:00:08.160
Who the hell is Meli?

1:00:08.480 --> 1:00:11.640
Suzan, how many times are you
going to ask the same question?

1:00:11.800 --> 1:00:15.320
The tranny you saw in my office.
How many times do I have to tell you?

1:00:15.600 --> 1:00:17.920
Look here, Deniz. Please come to your senses.

1:00:18.200 --> 1:00:19.200
You should better listen..

1:00:19.200 --> 1:00:21.040
No. You listen, little fool.

1:00:21.680 --> 1:00:25.320
Firstly, that is not your office, it's mine.

1:00:25.520 --> 1:00:29.320
Secondly, this isn't your home either, it is mine, too.

1:00:29.440 --> 1:00:30.080
Really?

1:00:30.480 --> 1:00:31.360
Thirdly

1:00:31.360 --> 1:00:34.600
and lastly, I don't have to put up with you,

1:00:34.800 --> 1:00:38.680
you'll be raping my rights because
of your weird relations with perverts.

1:00:39.960 --> 1:00:41.440
Now you hear me out.

1:00:41.640 --> 1:00:44.920
